                           <tr>
                              <td width="100%" class="TableCell"><b>From the bland city of Blaan to the Shores of FIre...</b><br>
                                 As written by N'riahn the Stout on July 27, 2004 6:54 AM
                                 <p></p>
                                 Somewhere between the Jerris and the Mist Swamps, as vague a geographical location as it may be, is the unexciting village
                                 of Blaan.  Sporting all manner of goods and services and being located right on a major trade route, though a promising start,
                                 did not mean people would stay in Blaan.  Only when forced to stay by heavy rains did trade caravans stay in town, and took
                                 advantage of the local Smithy, the Tavern, and the Brothel.<p/>It was on such a night that I was conceived.<p/>That's right:
                                 My mother was a prostitute, and my father was a traveller I will never meet.  Perhaps the rains that forced my conception
                                 we're an omen from the Elements, along with my persistent meddling with puddles of mud, the nearby Mists, and other local
                                 natural phenomenon.<p/>Regardless, I was discovered by a travelling dwarf who tackled the way of the Elementalist, and took
                                 me to the Death's Sea where my training would commence.  My only loss was Nana, a local widow in Blaan who took the job of
                                 raising me while my mother continued her nocturnal exploits.<p/>Her parting gift to me, a yellow, silken scarf, would become
                                 my grimoire.
                                 <br></td>
                           </tr>
                        </table>
